node.text:
I’ve gone back and forth over the last week on whether or not I wanted to share this story I posted to my feed... after messaging back and forth with so many of you who feel exactly what I feel, who feel the pain I’ve felt many times over... today it’s important for me to share this message one more time

There’s always some standard of beauty that you’re not meeting. ‘Cause if you’re thin enough then you don’t have that ass that everyone wants. But if you have enough weight on you to have an ass, then your stomach isn’t flat enough. It’s all just ... impossible -Taylor Swift

Everyday there is someone online who feels the need to leave me a nasty comment or send me a CRUEL direct message or repost me to their story to exemplify something they do not agree with

I am SO sick and tired of strangers online telling us HOW we should look, WHAT we should eat... last week I was too thin and this week I’m overweight, bloated and don’t look “fit” enough. I’m done

You. Are. Enough... and nobody should EVER make you feel like less of a person or make you question who you are or what you look like. We are so blessed to live inside this AMAZING body that holds us, allows us to walk and talk and breathe. Our body takes care of us so we need to take care of it INSTEAD OF constantly beating ourselves up for not meeting a standard of beauty strangers and society might place on us

So the next time you feel like you’re not enough, I hope my words can uplift you. I choose to be nothing but a positive light to you because in a world of so much hatred, negativity and cruel people and words... WHY ADD TO IT? Be a light and do not let ANYONE dim it. Please continue to shine and uplift others because we need more incredible women like you in this world!!! I love you. It’s a beautiful day to be alive💫

node.title: There’s ALWAYS some standard of beauty you’re NOT meeting✨

DO IT WITH ME! 6 MINUTE ab workout babyyyy 😅💦 using absolutely nothing but YOU... quick, simple and trust me lmao your core will be on HOT FIRE

7 EXERCISES
30S ON 20S REST

1️⃣ sprinter crunches
2️⃣ high plank around the worlds
3️⃣ swimmer crunches with single leg tuck in
4️⃣ feet together sit ups
5️⃣ low plank spider crunch
6️⃣ high side plank oblique crunch right
7️⃣ high side plank oblique crunch left

Rest 60S and if you’re up for it, LETS DO IT AGAIN👏🏼 Repeat circuit 2-3x 😩

node.text:
4-5 weight training sessions a week with 2-3 rest days! One of those rest days is usually a hot yogaaaaa day 🧘🏼‍♀️✨ currently training abs 1-3 times a week and for cardio... you know the drill 😅💦 1-2 HIIT sessions a week

I’ve learned to be more flexible with my workout schedule!! Life happens and sometimes I miss a workout or need to shift some workouts around and that’s OK👏🏼 be sure to give your body the rest and recovery it needs and most importantly, create a workout split that makes YOU happy and will push you to get your cute bum to the gym 🥰❤️

node.text:
Gymshark x Whitney Simmons

I’ve spent the last year grieving a friend I miss everyday, fighting depression and anxiety all while putting my heart into creating, designing and bringing each piece of this collection to life. It was my escape and in a way, a form of deep healing for me. I am so proud of this collection and the journey it reminds me of. I hope you feel beautiful when you put these pieces on and most importantly, I hope they remind you that there is something beautiful in everyday. How precious our lives are. That everyday is a beautiful day to be alive 🤎

The complete collection reveal and try-on is now live on my YouTube channel

9•16•21
📸 @alimitton 
Hair @machinedarine
Makeup @melissa.hurkman

BACK ATTACK 🥵❤️‍🔥🔥 hitting you today with this COMPLETE pull workout that’ll leave you feeling roasty and toastyyyy

1️⃣ conventional deadlifts 🤌🏼 for every set reps go down, weight goes up 👏🏼 10, 8, 6 then 4 reps

2️⃣ 3 sets of 8
landmine close grip row

3️⃣ 3 sets of 10
rotating hammer to wide bicep curl

4️⃣ 3 sets of 10
cable stretchers 💦💦

5️⃣ SUPERSET: 3 sets of 10
cable hammer curl
to high to low face pulls

6️⃣ finishing off with 3 sets of 15 supine pull ups

Wearing @gymsharkwomen training sweat shorts and sports bra

it’s a beautiful day to be alive 🦋 take care of yourself this week. YOU DESERVE THIS! Here’s a quick ab circuit to pop into a workout this week 💦🤍

the new @tolucaswim Monarch collection is now available 🥵 featuring this alessandra midi+ one piece in our monarch print

1️⃣ 15 single-leg tuck in crunch left
2️⃣ 15 single-leg tuck in crunch right
3️⃣ 20 alternating leg lifts
4️⃣ 20 swimmer crunches

rest and repeat 2-3x

node.text:
~attempting~ to make these chocolate chip banana pancakes 🥞🍌 by @thejoshelkin 😩 Okay listen…. the presentation was mediocre at best but the taste? SUPERB 🤌🏼

1️⃣ peel and cut banana in half, add skewer and pop mini chocolate chips into the sides of the banana
2️⃣ freeze for 20 minutes
3️⃣ dip frozen banana into your favorite pancake batter and fry for ~3 minutes on med-low
4️⃣ flip on its side, add 2 tbsp of water and cover to let the steam finish cooking the pancake

PRESENTATION 2/10 lol
EASE + TASTE 10/10

node.text: I’ve been placing so much of my energy and time into my personal healing journey 🦋 I’ve been fighting to make small but mighty changes each day into the things that make me feel alive again, to help lift the gravity of my personal wounds that as many of you know, have weighed me down so heavily this last year. I’m so happy to introduce you to the new @tolucaswim Monarch Collection 🦋 inspired by metamorphosis, celebrating the steps you’ve taken to show up as a better you today 🤍
